Decent place to grab some Mexican food. The portions are a bit small for their apps and their tacos so you`ll probably be full after spending over $30. I had the enchiladas this time and it was just your typical salsa verde with shredded chicken inside. Nothing spectacular.

The mimosa`s were great! Really strong and had some great flavour though :)</Text>

<user>117492160746601024506< /user>< Text>
Usually love to eat brunch here. We went a couple of weeks ago on a Sunday. It was Brunch time still but my wife wanted something from the lunch menu. Even though it was only 15 mins. the Executive Chef refused to take our order. Even our waiter was in disbelief. We took our business elsewhere. We will probably go back, we do like their food, specially brunch but the service needs to be a little more proactive to make sure they don't let the "rules" affect their customer service. Next time perhaps offer a cocktail to get your guests to wait the extra 15 mins?< /Text>

<Rate>5<//Rate>< Text>
Well, i'm pretty sure they are saving my baby's life right now with i-131. She was exhibiting many of the side effects common to the medication used in treating hyperthyroidism and it was become clear I-131 was the only thing that was going to keep my cat from deteriorating.

I had expended a significant amount of money at another vet on medical issues earlier in the  year before a diagnosis of her underlying hyperthyroidism and allergies. I had burned through 8k before finding out I no longer had the money to afford the treatment that would put my cats troubles to an end. I had to save for it no matter the sacrifice. Mean while she was not responding well to medication. Suffering complications, that kept setting me back from what I thought I needed to pay to get her treated in Davis. It was time I didn't have with how poorly the medication was working out. Dropping out of college for a few semesters and selling my car had occurred to me on a number of occasions by that point. When I learned Chico Cat Hospital was capable of doing the procedure for a price that while still steep was more manageable in this local economy I turned to my cat scooped her up and danced with her all the way around the house while I sobbed ugly tears. I could make it happen.

She is now resting comfortably on her favorite bed from home in her windowed enclosure, staring outside waiting for her radiation levels to diminish so I can take her home..I know this because their facility has a two way talk webcam that allows me to visit with her since she is currently radioactive and laws dictate I can't see her until her radiation levels fall off. I don't get particularly good sound on my end but she clearly responds to my voice and the important thing to me is that I can make her feel more comfortable.

So far the Staff at Chico Hospital for Cats have responded to my every helicopter parent email and call i've thrown at them. They've basically made me feel about as comfortable as I could theoretically be while my cat isn't home. (I've been a wreck leading up to and during this whole thing. My cat is my child, my whole freaking world. ) I feel foolish for having not come to a place that specializes in cats sooner. I thought sticking with someone who knew her history would result in the best care but it's painfully apparent no amount of history/experience can beat specialization in a field.

I'll spare details but when I took Meera in I promised her I would atone for the callous treatment she experienced at the hands of her former owner.  I've spent more money on her in the past 6 months than I survive on in a year as a broke college student to prove it.  I'd sell the shirt off my back if I thought it would make the difference. That's not an expression for me its a reality. For a second there I was worried I was going to fail to live up to that promise no matter what I sacrificed. I've never felt more torn up in my entire life.  I'm in tears just thinking about it now. Thanks to this establishment I've been able to keep my promise. I can't begin to express my gratitude. I simply don't know how.

Thank you to Dr. Colleran for your caring expertise. Thank you Sam and Bernadine for taking care of my baby while I can't.  Same to anyone else who see's to her before she comes home. As silly as it may sound to some....this cat saved my life. Thank you for helping me save hers.<//Text>

< text>
If I could give negative infinity starts, I would.  We hired Olympia after our mortgage company spent a year of refusing our payments due to the flooding  and the loss of our home to flooding (twice).  Our mortgage company says the home as a complete loss despite our county buying us out and moved to foreclose on the property- despite refusing our payments.  We agreed to let Hal Jeffery's and Sam Branco's team help us.

They stopped the auction, but never finished up the agreement which was to negotiate a new payment with our mortgage company.  We have not heard anything since March 13th, in the evening. Due to our house being a buyout property and we were relocated by the US government, the SBA could choose to foreclose and liquidate our current home as well, despite never missing payments on either mortgage.   They gave us documents to file, which we paid $300 for, but only received four pages.  We later learned that they were suppose to have given us an entire packet to file, which is why they ask for all of your financial information.

Needless to say, in addition to $3,000 in their fees, we are out $600 in fees to stop the auction of a house that is to be torn down by the county at some point.  The worst part of it all is our lender keeps sending us letters say we are willing to work with you, while last we heard from Sam Branco on March 13, they were going to call our lender again and call us right back.  All of our emails and phone calls have gone unanswered since then.

What their "plan of action" to stop the foreclosure was has caused so many credit problems, that it will be years before we will ever recover from.   This left us both wondering if it was worth doing the right thing with a flooded home and holding out for the buyout.   It really is offensive that they are fully aware of our situation and then they too take advantage of a family that has lost everything twice.

I am sharing this in hopes that others will consider the ramifications of one, hiring this law firm, despite the google reviews; and two, to consider the financial ramifications for what they suggest to stop an auction or foreclosure.

Lastly, don't just read my review or the reviews on google, look on Yelp and any other board that provides consumer feed back.  Olympia cannot can't spam bot them all into good ratings.< /text>

<Text>I came here for the first time to see if the place lived to its hype. It definitely does!
Firsr of all, the staff was great and had conversations with me as I was eating. Super friendly and great to speak with!
I went with Ike's Classic Rib Eye Steak Sandwich and an order of fries since I always like to go with what seems to be the staple of the restaurant on my first visit. BEST STEAK SANDWICH IN STOCKTON! Great steak texture, amazing in-house sauce, and fantastic bread choice (they get Genova Bakery breads). The fries were done amazingly.
My only complaint is that they close a bit earlier (about 6-8 pm). I've tried to go in the past after work but they were either closed or approaching closing time so I couldn't go. I can't blame them for that though; I don't wanna be at work all day either.

<name>Kit<//name>< Text>
7/15/19 @ 2:30ish

Very few have a I had a steak sandwich but never one like Fork It, there sandwiches are packed and loaded with so much flavor. I got the Ribeye classic boy you can taste how flavorful the meat is, it's tender, it's juicy, it's finger licking good! I got the 12" sandwich which is enough for 2 people to share with a side of fries, we were stuffed. I will definitely come back and try more, so much options I have to come back. I support my folks!

This is a locally own family business that just opened up. The owner and staff is very nice and pleasant to talk to who has great customer service. They take time in genuinely making the foods right on the other side of the counter. The inside eatery is a bit on the smaller side, it's perfect for a quick grab and go. Beverages they do only have can soda and bottled water, and some unsweetened tea (lemon and sugar provided). There prices are not bad at all in the quality food you get!</Text>

< Review>
I have purchased 4 Q-see camera systems in the last 8 years.
I recently purchase the QC 958. What a piece of junk.
I have a static ip, but the majority of it QC 958 programming is self programming with a roaming ip, which makes it hard for someone without a lot of program experience to set up with a static IP. They want you to use their 3rd party internet router provider.
Which I believe makes it easier for some to take over your internet.
My upload internet has been hijacked several times and was attacking other computers.  I do not know for sure that it is the new camera system, but my problems did not start until I installed it and the port that is being used to attack other computer is coming from the camera port.
Q-see has out sourced their tech support to India.  Trying to talk to someone in the U.S. seems to be impossible. " Good Luck".
They just lost my business and any references.
Ray Schill</Review>

< text>
My wife took me here after she got a gift card from work. The hostess and both our waitresses were friendly and attentive. I had the bacon cheeseburger while my wife had some kind of chicken sandwich. My wife's sandwich was "okay" according to her. We both had a helping of fries that could only be described as miserly so thanks for helping with my figure I guess. My burger was cooked precisely to rare which is actually how I like it (medium rare requested) but they failed to let it rest so it arrived at the table sopping with juices and strangely lukewarm. Further the house spread for the bun completely overpowered every other taste in the burger. If you can't taste the cheddar on the burger you have a problem. Honestly I hold the manager responsible. He or she is clearly unqualified. I'm embarrassed for whoever let such a sloppy excuse for an American classic exit their kitchen.< /text>

< text>
I always go to the Yard House during Happy Hour because they have one of the best. I'm not a big drinker, but half priced appetizers and pizzas will always keep me coming back for more. The Poke Nachos are my favorite and I still don't know how they pack so much flavor in them.  The pizzas are thin crust and the mozzarella cheese on the Margarita pizza is fresh, stringy when you pull it and delicious. The bar staff is quick to greet you, knowledgeable about the beers and the food, and super friendly.  I always recommend the one at Mission Valley and my wife and I stop there every time we go to the movies.  You will not be disappointed.<//text>

What exceptional service! It was a busy Saturday night, however we didn't have to wait long for a table.  The staff was very attentive and aimed to please.  My husbands steak was more so on the well side and he wanted medium. The manager offered to bring out a new one and my husband said no thank you.  10 minutes later the manager comes out with a new steak cooked to perfection.  The way this staff strives too keep their customers satisfied is not only surprising but truly remarkable. We were celebrating my husband's birthday and didn't tell them because my husband isn't one for big displays. You would think that they knew because of the great service they provided. Located directly next to the movie theater,  this is my favorite spot to grab a bite to eat and a drink either before or after taking in a movie. The main draw as with most Yard House restaurants is the the massive amount of beers on tap, so big it needs its own menu for itself.  The food is reasonably priced and covers the gambit from soups and salads to burgers and sandwiches to steak and chicken entrees.< /review>

The food is always really great and theres usually a very short wait if there is one. The place sits alot of people. It's more of a sports bar than your expect which means it can get really loud sometimes. So if you are trying to watch a game and have a huge variety of beers this is the place. Honestly this was probably the worst experience I've had a Yard House. The location was pretty empty and our server forgot about us. < text>
Great service, great beer selection with GREAT labeling, and clean environment. 5/5 in that regards.
However, as a sit down restaurant, the food was well below mediocre.  The onion rings were 90% batter, the fries were cold, and the burger was bad enough to warrant not finishing.

If you're coming here for a meeting or group event, absolutely get some beers, but skip the food!< /text>

This was my first time at Yardhouse, and I went because I had some gift cards to this restaurant. I went on a Monday night, it wasn't packed, and we were seated right away. They had football playing on the tv, which is nice if you wanna catch the game and grab a bite. We just went on a whim, and lucked out on going during their happy hour. We got half off our appetizers, so we got two instead of one. The best thing was they have vegan/vegetarian friendly option. I got buffalo Gardein wings, which is mock chicken, and it was soo delicious! My bf even liked them, and he's a meat eater. They have a whole section of the menu based on Gardein options. I got the blackened Gardein chicken torta and upgraded to truffle fries. On top of the delicious food, staff was friendly, and made sure we knew all our options on the menu, since it was our first time there. Good place to go with friends with good food. And you can catch a movie after, since AMC is right next door.< /text>

This was my first time at Yardhouse, and I went because I had some gift cards to this restaurant. I went on a Monday night, it wasn't packed, and we were seated right away. They had football playing on the tv, which is nice if you wanna catch the game and grab a bite. We just went on a whim, and lucked out on going during their happy hour.
